me.utk.networking

Interface MessageBuilder


  • public interface MessageBuilder
    A message builder which constructs messages from fragments sent over a network.

    Specific implementations can utilize custom markers, flags, or keywords to specify commands. There are no API requirements on this class other than the conditions specified in the method documentation.

    Version:
    December 8, 2020
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam

    • Method Detail

      • hasMoreMessages

        boolean hasMoreMessages()
        Returns true iff the nextMessage() method will be able to return a complete message on its next call.

        A message is considered complete when all of the information sent as a part of the message is received and coalesced into a single String[].

        Returns:
        true if a call to the nextMessage method will be able to successfully return a complete message; otherwise, false
        See Also:
        nextMessage()

      • nextMessage

        String[] nextMessage()
        Returns a not-null String[] containing the next complete message in the builder, if one exists.

        A message is considered complete when all of the information sent as a part of the message is received and coalesced into a single String[]. Callers can determine whether complete messages are available via the hasMoreMessages() method.

        If a complete message does not exist, this method's behavior is undefined. Implementations are free to return null, empty String[], prior or random messages, or throw Exceptions.

        This method guarantees that the returned completed message which be fragmented in exactly the same order and pattern as the original message. Any implementation which does not satisfy this guarantee should note that in its documentation.

        Returns:
        A String[] representing a single, complete message sent over the network, if one exists. Otherwise, behavior is undefined.
        See Also:
        hasMoreMessages()
